Package com.spectralogic.ds3client.helpers.strategy.channelstrategy

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ChannelPreparable
    When initiating data movement in a put or get, the source or destination channel my need some sort of preparation.
    ChannelStrategy
    An interface whose concrete subclasses specify the behavior used to read or write a channel.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    NullChannelPreparable
    When initiating data movement in a put or get, the source or destination channel my need some sort of preparation.
    RandomAccessChannelStrategy
    A subclass of ChannelStrategy that creates a channel per blob positioned at the offset correct for the current blob offset.
    SequentialChannelStrategy
    A subclass of ChannelStrategy used to provide "streamed" access to a channel, where streamed means that the channel will be accessed in sequentially increasing offsets.
    SequentialFileReaderChannelStrategy
    A subclass of ChannelStrategy that holds the instance of a channel a blob will during a put operation.
    SequentialFileWriterChannelStrategy
    A subclass of ChannelStrategy that holds the instance of a channel a blob will during a get operation.
    TruncatingChannelPreparable
    When initiating data movement in a put or get, the source or destination channel my need some sort of preparation.
